From: Pantelis Antoniou <panto@antoniou-consulting.com>
Date: Tue, 8 Jan 2013 20:43:29 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 45/54] lcdc_panel: panel access convert to get child node

of_find_node_by_name() is not what should be used here.
It does a global name search which is not what we want to do here.

Convert to the use the correct of_get_child_by_name() function.

Signed-off-by: Pantelis Antoniou <panto@antoniou-consulting.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/lcdc/lcdc_panel.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/lcdc/lcdc_panel.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/lcdc/lcdc_panel.c
index 29a0952..037e2d2 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/lcdc/lcdc_panel.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/lcdc/lcdc_panel.c
@@ -334,7 +334,7 @@ static struct lcdc_panel_info * of_get_panel_info(struct device_node *np)
 		return NULL;
 	}
 
-	info_np = of_find_node_by_name(np, "panel-info");
+	info_np = of_get_child_by_name(np, "panel-info");
 	if (!info_np) {
 		pr_err("%s: could not find panel-info node\n", __func__);
 		return NULL;
